Path: godot/tutorials/rendering/viewports.rst
Summary: This section explains how Viewports handle input events for their child nodes, including SubViewports and SubViewportContainers.
Viewports are also responsible for delivering properly adjusted and scaled input events to their children nodes. By default SubViewports don't automatically receive input, unless they receive it from their direct SubViewportContainer parent node. In this case, input can be disabled with the Gui Disable Input property.

For more information on how Godot handles input, please read the Input Event Tutorial.
---CHUNK---
Document: Viewports Tutorial
Path: godot/tutorials/rendering/viewports.rst
Summary: This section explains how to enable a Viewport as a listener for 3D sound.
A Viewport needs to be enabled as a listener for 3D sound to be audible. This applies to both 2D and 3D nodes. If a SubViewport is used to display a World3D or World2D, ensure the listener is enabled for it.
